},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s6_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9a171e",
"children":[
"Hypersensitivity pneumonitis occurs through organic antigen exposure (e.g., agricultural dusts, thermophilic fungi, bacteria)."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"1b19cc",
"children":[
"Fever, cough, and fatigue develop 12 hours later."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"0b2f0f",
"children":[
"Physical examination reveals inspiratory crackles."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s6_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cbf395",
"children":[
"Chest x-ray may be normal or show diffuse micronodular disease. ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"high-resolution computed tomography",
"children":[
"HRCT"
]
},
" shows diffuse centrilobular micronodules and ground-glass opacities."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_pm_s6_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"17b21f",
"children":[
"Antigen removal results in resolution of symptoms in 48 hours. Glucocorticoids are provided for severe symptoms."
]
}
]
}
]
